text: Elk Grove is a city in Sacramento County, California. It is just south of Sacramento. In 2020, 176,124 people lived there. This makes it the second- largest city in Sacramento County, after Sacramento. The city was first incorporated on July 1, 2000. ==References== Category:Cities in California Category:Settlements in Sacramento County, California Category:2000 establishments in the United States Category:2000s establishments in California
